[The manifestations of tularemia in the reported cases are not specified. Tularemia can present in a number of ways based on the mode of acquisition. The acquisition of _F. tularensis_ can be from tick and deer fly bites, skin contact with infected animals, ingestion of contaminated food or water, laboratory exposure, and inhalation of contaminated dusts or aerosols. - Mod.LL]

